track_notes: At the end of this track there is a grass triangle where the track meets the road and we parked on that. We walked over Bwlch y Garn on the way up, (38 mins to summit) this was pointless. This track which we came down on is a wiser route up and back in my opinion...
track_title: Rough track so we parked near houses in Nantyglo

track_notes: Total time (including ops): 1hr 20m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T1. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. track_title: Mynydd Carn-y-cefn Linear from East. Feb 2020.

track_notes:
Parking available at Ebbw Vale Parkway station, free at the time.
Follow path across railway line to the main road, cross over and head up the side street then up stairs between the streets.
Follow track up to the reservoir then path behind wall/fence.  Path is wet in places.
Turn right somewhere and follow tracks up onto the hill and head for the summit.  I think there are more direct routes than the ones I took but they were narrow on a steep slope and did not fancy them in gale force winds.
